title: Lebanon reverses controversial decision to delay clocks change
description: Lebanon's government has reversed a controversial decision to delay the start of daylight saving time by a month.

title: FIFA set to pay clubs £300m for sending players to World Cup
description: FIFA is set to pay clubs around £300m for sending players to the 2026 World Cup in a huge cash uplift, Sky News understands.

title: Orlando Bloom tells President Zelenskyy 'strength' of Ukrainian people is 'awe-inspiring'
description: Orlando Bloom has praised the "incredible stoic nature" of the Ukrainian people as he met with President Volodymyr Zelenskyy and encouraged him to "go win" the war.

title: Singer Linda Nolan reveals cancer has spread to her brain and she is preparing for 'inevitable'
description: Singer Linda Nolan has revealed her cancer has spread to her brain.

title: Global population could fall to six billion with 'unprecedented investment'
description: The global population could fall to six billion by the end of the century if there is "unprecedented investment" in tackling poverty and inequality, researchers have said.

title: UK and European markets calm but warning of 'slow motion' problem to come
description: After a turbulent Friday and the rumbling of the worst financial crisis since 2008, the UK and European stock markets have largely calmed.

title: Passenger 'opens plane door and triggers emergency slide'
description: An "unruly passenger" has been detained after allegedly opening an emergency exit door on a plane, triggering the emergency slide.

title: Netanyahu delays controversial overhaul of Israel's judiciary, says coalition partner
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has delayed controversial plans to reform Israel's judiciary, his coalition partners say.

title: Buyer found for Silicon Valley Bank
description: A buyer has been found for the collapsed Silicon Valley Bank, the bank whose downfall heralded the financial unrest still being felt across the banking world.

title: North Korea fires two test missiles as US deploys carrier group to South Korea for drills
description: North Korea has fired two test missiles as its neighbour South Korea begins joint military drills with the US.

title: 'Come to your senses now!' Israel's president tells Netanyahu to halt reforms as sacking sparks mass protests
description: Israel's president has called on Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to "stop the legislative process immediately" after the PM triggered widespread protests by sacking his defence minister for objecting to judicial reforms.

title: US urges Israel to 'find compromise' after Netanyahu sacks defence minister, sparking mass protests
description: The White House has urged Israel "to find a compromise as soon as possible" after Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu sacked his defence minister for objecting to judicial reforms, triggering widespread protests.
